This paper deals with the problem of model selection for Gaussian process classifiers using different optimization criteria. The paper discusses the use of Leave-One-Out Cross Validation (LOO CV) and Expectation Propagation (EP) approximation to arrive at approximate LOO predictive distributions. The paper also considers smoothed versions of criteria such as F-measure and Weighted Error Rate (WER) for handling imbalanced data. Given these topics, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses experiments on several real-world benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
